        "Our neural network mostly stays stuck at around a loss of $1.0$ and later around $0.85$-$0.90$ Given that this loss didn't decrease much, we can assume that this learning rate being too high, also caused the model to get stuck in a **local minimum**, which we'll learn more about soon. Iterating over more epochs, doesn't seem helpful at this point, which tells us that we're likely stuck with our optimization. Does this mean that this is the most we can get from our optimizer on this dataset?\n",
